article.description: Antwoine Anderson sank a 3-pointer with a second left in double overtime and Fordham beat Saint Joseph's 86-83 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Fordham rallies late to stun Saint Joseph's 86-83 in 2OT
article.linkText: Fordham rallies late to stun Saint Joseph's 86-83 in 2OT
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Antwoine Anderson sank a 3-pointer with a second left in double overtime and Fordham beat Saint Joseph's 86-83 on Saturday night. Anderson -- who finished with 20 points -- made the long-distance jumper after Saint Joseph's tied it at 83 with seven seconds to go in double OT. Prokop Slanina added 15 points for the Rams (10-13, 4-6 Atlantic 10). Christian Sengfelder and Joseph Chartouny had 12 apiece. The Hawks (10-12, 3-7) had a 15-point advantage with 9:44 to play in regulation but Fordham battled to a 62-61 lead on a Sengfelder 3-pointer with 19 seconds left. The Hawks were back up 64-62 when Chartouny sank a layup at the buzzer to tie it at 64 and into the first overtime. The Rams led 75-73 with five seconds left in the first OT when the Hawks' Lamarr Kimble sank two free throws to send the game into double overtime. Kimble scored 24 points for the Hawks. Charlie Brown had 22.
